    q: "A nurse is assessing a client with severe burns covering 35% of the total body surface area who was admitted 48 hours ago. The nurse notes a drop in urine output from 50 mL/hr to 15 mL/hr despite adequate IV fluid resuscitation. Serum creatinine has risen from 1.0 to 2.8 mg/dL. Which complication should the nurse suspect?",
