    q: "A nurse is performing the Parkland formula calculation for a client who sustained full-thickness burns over 40% TBSA. The client weighs 80 kg and was burned 1 hour ago. How much IV Lactated Ringer's solution should be administered in the first 8 hours from the time of injury?",
    o: ["6,400 mL total over the first 24 hours", "12,800 mL in the first 8 hours from the time of injury", "6,400 mL in the first 8 hours from the time of injury", "3,200 mL in the first 8 hours from the time of injury"],
